&lt;p&gt;Band 5 Community Staff Nurse - Intermediate Care Team (Acute Response Team)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A great opportunity has arisen to join the Intermediate Care Team (Acute Response Team).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking fo an enthusiastic nurse who is forward thinking with a passion for nursing to join our friendly team on a fixed term contract to cover Maternity Leave until 25th July 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should possess excellent communication skills, enjoy working as part of a team, be able to work independently, carry out comprehensive assessments, plan, implement and evaluate delivery of complex nursing interventions as part of the holistic approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are dynamic, organised, work well within the multidisciplinary team and have an interest in caring for people in their own home including IV therapies, End of life care, Wound care and responding to the need for out of hours nursing interventions for patients with various acute and chronic conditions we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability and means to travel between patients in a timely manner is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A secondment may be considered but applicants will need to seek agreement with their current line manager prior to application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post. English and /or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held 26th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
